The paper deals with the problem of estimating an unknown signal from noisy, linear measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and machine learning. The approach used is via solving a regularized M-estimator, which is a popular method in these fields. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Statistics (cs.ST), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
